1598
01:28:47.104 --> 01:28:51.024
Thank you for the opportunity to appear, and I am here to speak to the practical

1599
01:28:51.124 --> 01:28:55.064
implications of the proposed amendments to the Data and Statistics Census

1600
01:28:55.124 --> 01:28:58.604
Framework and the increased reliance on administrative

1601
01:28:58.684 --> 01:28:59.164
data.

1602
01:29:01.024 --> 01:29:04.324
I acknowledge that under the Data and Statistics Act 2022,

1603
01:29:04.504 --> 01:29:08.404
agencies are authorized to collect, share, and integrate data

1604
01:29:08.464 --> 01:29:11.674
for statistical purposes. I also acknowledge that

1605
01:29:11.724 --> 01:29:15.664
administrative data and data matching are established tools within the

1606
01:29:15.683 --> 01:29:19.394
government systems, including the electoral context under the Electoral

1607
01:29:19.564 --> 01:29:23.204
Act 1993. My submission is not that these

1608
01:29:23.244 --> 01:29:27.184
powers should not exist. My submission is that expanding reliance

1609
01:29:27.224 --> 01:29:30.684
on them in place of a comprehensive census introduces

1610
01:29:30.844 --> 01:29:33.344
material risks that are not currently mitigated.

1611
01:29:34.324 --> 01:29:38.004
The proposed direction shifts the system away from a

1612
01:29:38.014 --> 01:29:41.744
direct population-wide self-reported census towards a

1613
01:29:41.784 --> 01:29:45.774
model that relies on administrative data, data integration, and

1614
01:29:45.844 --> 01:29:49.084
statistical modeling. This is not a minor change.

1615
01:29:49.204 --> 01:29:52.424
It is a structural change to how population reality is

1616
01:29:52.444 --> 01:29:56.384
constructed. A full census provides a baseline that

1617
01:29:56.404 --> 01:30:00.104
is directly sourced from individuals, standardized across the

1618
01:30:00.164 --> 01:30:02.944
population, and independently verifiable.

1619
01:30:03.744 --> 01:30:06.004
Administrative data does not provide that.

1620
01:30:06.084 --> 01:30:08.324
It reflects who interacts with services,

1621
01:30:08.584 --> 01:30:12.474
what those services collect, and

1622
01:30:12.544 --> 01:30:16.004
how systems are designed. As a result, the

1623
01:30:16.014 --> 01:30:19.894
dataset begins to reflect the system and not the population.

1624
01:30:20.944 --> 01:30:23.994
Groups that engage less with services are recorded

1625
01:30:24.024 --> 01:30:27.864
inconsistently or are not fully captured by existing systems,

1626
01:30:28.084 --> 01:30:31.804
and they will be underrepresented. That's not a possibility.

1627
01:30:31.864 --> 01:30:33.284
That's an expected outcome.

1628
01:30:34.204 --> 01:30:37.644
Many administrative systems were never designed for statistical

1629
01:30:37.724 --> 01:30:41.404
completeness. They do not ask the same questions, use consistent

1630
01:30:41.464 --> 01:30:45.084
definitions, or capture information in a way that is

1631
01:30:45.124 --> 01:30:48.664
comparable across agencies. This leads to gaps,

1632
01:30:48.904 --> 01:30:52.364
inconsistent classification, and reliance on estimation.

1633
01:30:52.964 --> 01:30:56.384
When that data is aggregated and modeled, those limitations

1634
01:30:56.424 --> 01:30:59.744
compound. As reliance on modeling increases,

1635
01:31:00.284 --> 01:31:03.294
outputs may appear complete, but appearance is not the same as

1636
01:31:03.364 --> 01:31:06.920
accuracy.When data is incomplete at

1637
01:31:06.980 --> 01:31:10.780
source and used to generate inferred results, the final data set

1638
01:31:10.840 --> 01:31:14.400
is built on assumptions that are not always visible or

1639
01:31:14.440 --> 01:31:15.020
testable.

1640
01:31:15.940 --> 01:31:19.840
This creates a condition where decisions are made on data that cannot be

1641
01:31:19.880 --> 01:31:23.800
fully verified against reality. Alongside these risks, there

1642
01:31:23.840 --> 01:31:27.190
is a second issue. Data is collected under specific

1643
01:31:27.300 --> 01:31:31.150
conditions for a defined purpose, under a particular authority,

1644
01:31:31.280 --> 01:31:34.740
and within a specific context. Under the current and

1645
01:31:34.800 --> 01:31:38.600
proposed framework, data can be moved, combined, and reused

1646
01:31:38.680 --> 01:31:42.560
across systems. However, there is no consistent mechanism to

1647
01:31:42.580 --> 01:31:46.100
ensure that authority and context travel with that

1648
01:31:46.200 --> 01:31:49.560
data, and this simply means that systems are not required to

1649
01:31:49.600 --> 01:31:53.060
demonstrate that the use remains consistent with the original

1650
01:31:53.120 --> 01:31:56.720
purpose, and that authority remains valid, or that the

1651
01:31:56.780 --> 01:32:00.410
context has been preserved. Authority is

1652
01:32:00.440 --> 01:32:04.420
assumed rather than verified. In a system increasingly

1653
01:32:04.480 --> 01:32:08.080
reliant on integrated and modeled data, this creates a

1654
01:32:08.120 --> 01:32:11.840
material governance gap. Decisions are made using data where the

1655
01:32:11.880 --> 01:32:15.340
original purpose is unclear, the authority cannot be

1656
01:32:15.400 --> 01:32:18.660
demonstrated, and the context has been lost.

1657
01:32:18.720 --> 01:32:22.680
In any other regulatory environment, that would be considered a failure of

1658
01:32:22.720 --> 01:32:26.370
control. This matters because the point of risk is no longer

1659
01:32:26.460 --> 01:32:30.380
collection, it is use. If a system cannot demonstrate that

1660
01:32:30.420 --> 01:32:34.320
it has authority to use data in a given context at the point it

1661
01:32:34.360 --> 01:32:38.120
is being used, then the legitimacy of the decision cannot be

1662
01:32:38.180 --> 01:32:42.080
assured. The census also provides an independent point

1663
01:32:42.100 --> 01:32:45.780
of validation. It allows governments to check administrative

1664
01:32:45.840 --> 01:32:49.740
data, identify inconsistencies, and confirm whether outputs

1665
01:32:49.780 --> 01:32:52.080
align with the population.

1666
01:32:53.120 --> 01:32:57.000
If that function is reduced, there is no equivalent mechanism

1667
01:32:57.040 --> 01:33:00.750
to replace it. Without an independent benchmark, the system

1668
01:33:00.820 --> 01:33:04.380
becomes self-referential. These risks apply across the

1669
01:33:04.400 --> 01:33:07.840
population, but they are amplified for Māori.

1670
01:33:08.460 --> 01:33:12.120
The census is currently the only mechanism that allows Māori to

1671
01:33:12.160 --> 01:33:15.540
self-identify at scale and in a consistent way.

1672
01:33:16.139 --> 01:33:19.040
No administrative system replaces that function.

1673
01:33:19.340 --> 01:33:22.560
Administrative systems do not consistently capture

1674
01:33:22.980 --> 01:33:26.520
Māori identity, iwi or hapū affiliation.

1675
01:33:27.220 --> 01:33:31.100
And if reliance shifts to those systems, Māori are more

1676
01:33:31.140 --> 01:33:35.060
likely to be undercounted, misclassified, or simply

1677
01:33:35.140 --> 01:33:38.940
not captured at all. At that point, underrepresentation

1678
01:33:38.980 --> 01:33:42.700
becomes structural, and over time, this reduces visibility.

1679
01:33:44.080 --> 01:33:47.540
Reduced visibility has direct consequences like

1680
01:33:47.600 --> 01:33:51.400
funding, services, and policy decisions, because

1681
01:33:51.460 --> 01:33:54.920
that all follows data. If Māori are not fully

1682
01:33:55.020 --> 01:33:58.500
visible in that data, they are not fully reflected in those

1683
01:33:58.520 --> 01:34:02.120
decisions. And there is also a contextual risk.

1684
01:34:02.680 --> 01:34:06.410
Māori data is connected to identity, whakapapa, and

1685
01:34:06.460 --> 01:34:10.310
collective representation. When it is removed from its original

1686
01:34:10.340 --> 01:34:14.160
context and combined with other data sets and reused, its

1687
01:34:14.240 --> 01:34:17.740
meaning can change. Without mechanisms to carry forward

1688
01:34:17.800 --> 01:34:21.410
context and authority, outputs may appear valid but not

1689
01:34:21.500 --> 01:34:23.600
accurately reflect Māori reality.

1690
01:34:24.410 --> 01:34:26.940
The effects of this shift will accumulate over time.

1691
01:34:27.340 --> 01:34:31.160
Small inaccuracies will become embedded, gaps become

1692
01:34:31.180 --> 01:34:35.020
normalized, decisions become incomplete or decontextualized,

1693
01:34:35.160 --> 01:34:38.860
data begin to shape outcomes. Without a reliable

1694
01:34:38.960 --> 01:34:42.880
baseline and without the ability to verify authority and context

1695
01:34:42.940 --> 01:34:45.780
at the point of use, that cannot be corrected.

1696
01:34:46.750 --> 01:34:49.700
There is also an accountability issue.

1697
01:34:49.740 --> 01:34:53.120
The census currently provides a reference point to assess

1698
01:34:53.130 --> 01:34:56.910
representation, track disparities, and evaluate whether

1699
01:34:56.940 --> 01:35:00.590
commitments are being met. And if that reference point is

1700
01:35:00.640 --> 01:35:04.580
weakened, it becomes significantly harder to demonstrate whether outcomes

1701
01:35:04.640 --> 01:35:08.440
align with reality. This is not just a data issue,

1702
01:35:08.580 --> 01:35:12.360
it is a governance issue. In the electoral context, the

1703
01:35:12.400 --> 01:35:16.040
implications extend further. Data is used to maintain

1704
01:35:16.080 --> 01:35:19.400
electoral roll, confirm eligibility, and support

1705
01:35:19.440 --> 01:35:23.200
participation. If that data is incomplete or used

1706
01:35:23.240 --> 01:35:26.420
without verified authority, there is a risk to the

1707
01:35:26.459 --> 01:35:28.640
integrity of those processes.

1708
01:35:29.480 --> 01:35:32.620
This submission does not argue against administrative data.

1709
01:35:32.690 --> 01:35:36.520
It argues that it cannot replace a comprehensive census

1710
01:35:37.020 --> 01:35:39.840
without introducing systemic risk.

1711
01:35:40.340 --> 01:35:42.980
If the committee is minded to pro- ...

1712
01:35:44.420 --> 01:35:46.400
to proceed, then at a minimum,

1713
01:35:47.480 --> 01:35:51.240
data used for statistical or decision-making purposes must

1714
01:35:51.300 --> 01:35:55.110
carry verifiable information on its origin, authority,

1715
01:35:55.260 --> 01:35:59.160
and context, and systems must be able to demonstrate at the point of

1716
01:35:59.300 --> 01:36:02.140
use that the data remains valid for that purpose.

1717
01:36:02.700 --> 01:36:05.380
The issue is not whether government can use data, it is-

